US president Donald Trump is misinformed about South Africa’s planned land reforms, President Cyril Ramaphosa’s spokeswoman said on Thursday, after Trump tweeted that land was being seized by government from white farmers. Read: Trump says has asked Secretary of State to look at SA land seizures, farm killings Read: Trump tweet won’t affect SA-US relations – cabinet minister “The presidency has noted Trump’s tweet, which is misinformed in our view,” Khusela Diko said. “We will take up the matter through diplomatic channels.”